# UK PHV Platform — Project Rules

## Architecture

- Turborepo monorepo: `apps/api` (NestJS), `apps/web` (Next.js), `packages/*` (shared). Mobile (`apps/mobile`) is out of scope — not in the pnpm workspace.
- Feature-based modules in API: `modules/<domain>/` with `*.module.ts`, `*.service.ts`, `*.controller.ts`, `repositories/`.
- Never bypass repository layer for Prisma access from controllers.
- Use `@uk-phv/shared-types` for cross-app contracts; `@uk-phv/validation` for Zod schemas.

## API Response Standard

All HTTP responses use the envelope from `@uk-phv/shared-types`:

```typescript
{ success: true, data: T, meta: { requestId, timestamp, version } }
{ success: false, error: { code, message, details? }, meta }
```

Never return raw Prisma models from controllers — map to DTOs/summary types.

## TypeScript

- Strict mode always. No `any`. No `@ts-ignore` without linked issue.
- Prefer `type` imports: `import type { X } from '...'`.
- Use Zod for runtime validation at API boundaries; class-validator only where Nest pipes require it.

## Git & Commits

- Conventional commits: `feat(api):`, `fix(web):`, `chore(deps):`
- Scopes: api, web, shared-types, validation, docker, docs, compliance

## Compliance (Wolverhampton PHV)

- Booking records must set `retentionExpiresAt` on create (minimum 2 years).
- Dispatch must validate PHV driver + vehicle licences before assignment.
- All dispatch, complaint, and safeguarding actions require audit log entries.
- Never log PII, passwords, or tokens (see logger redaction).

## File Organization

```
apps/api/src/modules/<feature>/
  <feature>.module.ts
  <feature>.controller.ts
  <feature>.service.ts
  repositories/<feature>.repository.ts
  dto/ (optional)
```

## Do Not

- Add placeholder `TODO` implementations in production paths — implement or create a tracked issue in roadmap.
- Duplicate validation schemas — extend `@uk-phv/validation`.
- Put business logic in controllers or gateways.
